com.feathersui.maven.plugin.lime_openfl

Class Meta

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.feathersui.maven.plugin.lime_openfl.Meta

  • public class Meta
extends Object
    Represents the <meta> element of the Lime project.xml format.

    The following example sets the title and description fields. 

     
 <limeProject>
   <meta>
     <title>My Cool Application</title>
     <description>Get more stuff done with My Cool App</description>
   </meta>
 </limeProject>
    See Also:
    Lime project.xml format: <meta>

    • Field Detail

      • title

        public String title
        The title of the application. Represents the <meta title=""> attribute of the Lime project.xml format.

        Hint: If the <title> element is not defined, the default value will be populated from the project name in the Maven pom.xml file.

        The following example sets the <title> element. 

         
 <limeProject>
   <meta>
     <title>My Application</title>
   </meta>
 </limeProject>

      • description

        public String description
        The description of the application. Represents the <meta description=""> attribute of the Lime project.xml format.

        Hint: If the <description> element is not defined, the default value will be populated from the project description in the Maven pom.xml file.

        The following example sets the <description> element. 

         
 <limeProject>
   <meta>
     <description>Get more stuff done with My Cool App</description>
   </meta>
 </limeProject>

      • packageId

        public String packageId
        The package identifier of the application. Represents the <meta package=""> attribute of the Lime project.xml format.

        Hint: If the <packageId> element is not defined, the default value will be populated from the project description in the Maven pom.xml file.

        The following example sets the <packageId> element. 

         
 <limeProject>
   <meta>
     <packageId>com.example.myapp</packageId>
   </meta>
 </limeProject>

 </limeProject>

      • company

        public String company
        The name of the company that created the application. Represents the <meta company=""> attribute of the Lime project.xml format.

        Hint: If the <company> element is not defined, the default value will be populated from the organization name in the Maven pom.xml file.

        The following example sets the <company> element. 

         
 <limeProject>
   <meta>
     <company>Example, Inc.</company>
   </meta>
 </limeProject>

        public String companyUrl
